 is the number of days in a year.
 Therefore the probability that a day is an unbirthday of a certain student
 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
P_{1} & = & (D-1)/D\\
 & = & 1-\frac{1}{D},
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If there are 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 students, where 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 times as large as the number of days in a year (i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $N=\alpha D$
\end_inset

), in the school, the probability that a day is no student's birthday is
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray*}
P_{N}=P_{1}^{N} & = & (1-\frac{1}{D})^{N}\\
 & = & (1-\frac{1}{D})^{\alpha D}
\end{eqnarray*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
